# Install

## [AUR](https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/{{ expand('%:p:h:h:h:t') }})

```sh
yay -S {{ expand('%:p:h:h:h:t') }}
```

## [NixOS](https://nixos.org)

Add the following code to `/etc/nixos/configuration.nix`:

```nix
{ config, pkgs, ... }:
{
  nix.settings.experimental-features = [ "flakes" ];
  environment.systemPackages =
    let
      {{ expand('%:p:h:h:h:t') }} = (
        builtins.getFlake "github:{{ split(g:snips_github, '/')[-1] }}/{{ expand('%:p:h:h:h:t') }}"
      ).packages.${builtins.currentSystem}.default;
    in
    [
      {{ expand('%:p:h:h:h:t') }}
    ];
}
```

## [nix](https://github.com/NixOS/nix)

```sh
nix shell github:{{ split(g:snips_github, '/')[-1] }}/{{ expand('%:p:h:h:h:t') }}
```

Or just take a try without installation:

```sh
nix run github:{{ split(g:snips_github, '/')[-1] }}/{{ expand('%:p:h:h:h:t') }} -- --help
```

## [PYPI](https://pypi.org/project/{{ expand('%:p:h:h:h:t') }})

```sh
pip install {{ expand('%:p:h:h:h:t') }}
```

See [requirements](requirements) to know `extra_requires`.
